<TITLE> Ittefaq faces defamation suit </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 29 (bdnews24.com)A defamation case was filed on Tuesday against the top four officials of the Daily Ittefaq including one of the owners Mainul Hosein and editor Rahat Khan. Two businessmen, Shawkat Ali Khan Bipul and Haider Ali Khan Bulbul, also brothers, filed the case with Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court in the morning. The two other defendants are publisher of the daily Saju Hosein and reporter Zamiul Hossain Shipu. Metropolitan magistrate AKM Emdadul Haque will hear the case on Wednesday. The case details say a story the daily carried on Sep 16 headlined, "Terrorism in Mirpur, 125 enlisted by RAB" called the brothers "terrorists". It said the report was "totally wrong, planned and defamatory". bd
